  "description": {
    "en": "Learn pytest — the most popular Python testing framework. Write concise tests with plain assert, use fixtures for setup, and parametrize to test many inputs at once.",
    "ta": "மிகவும் பிரபலமான Python testing framework-ஐ கற்றுக்கொள்ளுங்கள். assert-உடன் சுருக்கமான சோதனைகள் எழுதுங்கள், fixtures மற்றும் parametrize பயன்படுத்துங்கள்."
  },
  "xp_reward": 55,
  "story_variants": {
    "en": "## Vaathiyaar's Shortcut\n\nVaathiyaar grins. \"You learned unittest — the formal way. Now let me show you pytest — the smart way. Less boilerplate, more power. In the real world, 80% of Python projects use pytest.\"\n\n### Why pytest?\n- **No classes needed** — just write functions starting with `test_`\n- **Plain assert** — no need for `assertEqual`, pytest gives rich diffs\n- **Fixtures** — reusable setup with `@pytest.fixture`\n- **Parametrize** — test many inputs with one function\n- **Plugins** — 800+ plugins on PyPI\n\n### Fixtures: Smart Setup\n\n```python\n@pytest.fixture\ndef sample_list():\n    return [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]\n\ndef test_sum(sample_list):\n    assert sum(sample_list) == 15\n```\n\n### Parametrize: Many Inputs, One Test\n\n```python\n@pytest.mark.parametrize('input,expected', [\n    (1, 1), (2, 4), (3, 9), (4, 16)\n])\ndef test_square(input, expected):\n    assert input ** 2 == expected\n```\n\n> **Key Concept:** pytest makes testing feel natural. You write plain Python assertions, and pytest handles the rest — discovery, reporting, and rich error messages."
  },
